26/01/2003
DAVOS, Switzerland -- US Secretary of State Colin Powell met Turkish Prime Minister Abdullah Gul and Justice and Development Party leader Recep Tayyip Erdogan to discuss the situation in neighbouring Iraq.
In comments after the meeting, the Turkish leaders signalled that the country's parliament would like to see a UN Security Council resolution before deciding whether the country's territory could be used in an operation against the Baghdad regime.
Powell said the US administration has a complete understanding of the "political situation and .
parliamentary situation" in Turkey.
(AP, AFP, Reuters - 25/01/03)
